1 olive oil
1 pear
½ head cos lettuce
1 carrot
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet mayonnaise
1.5 tbs soy sauce
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 packet Sichuan garlic paste

• Thinly slice pear. Shred cos lettuce (see ingredients). Grate the carrot.
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.

Little cooks: Help wash and tear the cos lettuce!

• In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise and half the Sichuan garlic paste. Set aside.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add the soy sauce, remaining Sichuan garlic paste and a splash of water. Turn chicken to coat. Set aside.
• Meanwhile, microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

Little cooks: Help warm the tortillas with oven gloves and under adult supervision. Be careful, the plate can get hot!

• Spread each tortilla with some Sichuan garlic mayo, then top with some cos lettuce, carrot, pear and glazed chicken.
• Sprinkle with crushed peanuts to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the tacos!